Bump version to jira-wiki-markup-1.5.0

Fix parsing of backslash char before non-icons

A backslash is not an escape character but is literal if it preceeds a
character sequence that would be an icon if it wasn't followed by an
alphanumeric char.

Fix handling of icon sequences at the start of a word

Special characters must only be escaped if the character sequence would
otherwise be interpreted as an emoji, e.g. `:Pa` and `:P2`.
